<DOC><DOCNO> AP890802-0036 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-02-89 0434EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Salvador-Battle     08-02 0219</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Salvador-Battle,0224</SECOND><HEAD>Rebels Attack Army Post in Capital</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leftist guerrillas attacked anarmy post in the capital in a battle that forced thousands ofresidents to run for cover. At least two people were reportedkilled.   The guerrillas attacked at dusk Tuesday from their camps on theslopes of the San Salvador Volcano that looms over the city'snorthwest.   The battle lasted about two hours and one soldier and onecivilian were reported killed. Two civilians and a soldier werewounded.   The battle kept thousands of residents of the San Ramonneighborhood huddled behind walls or vehicles. Automatic weapons'fire was heard from the northern neighborhoods of Zacamil andMejicanos, but there was no immediate word on casualties from thosezones.   It was the fifth time in eight months that the army post in SanRamon has been attacked. An estimated 200 rebels are camped on thevolcano.   Sgt. Ventura Lopez, commander of the detachment of 10 soldiersat the post, said there were about 60 attackers who hurled TNT.About 100 army reinforcements later joined the battle.   Rebels of the leftist Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front,fighting for 10 years to overthrow the U.S.-backed government, havestepped up attacks in the capital over the past 10 months after athree-year lull.</TEXT></DOC>